<HEADLINE>
<P>
UCLA WOMEN PLAY STANFORD IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The UCLA women's volleyball team, ranked second in the country, will try to 
remain undefeated in the Pacific 10 Conference when it plays host to Stanford 
tonight at 7 at Pauley Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
Stanford, which opened the season ranked second, has fallen to sixth nationally 
after losing to unranked Oregon last Saturday. The Cardinal is 8-3 overall. 
</P>
<P>
The Bruins, whose only loss was to top-ranked Hawaii on Sept. 8, are 9-1 
overall and lead the Pac-10 at 4-0. The Bruins have won 22 consecutive Pac-10 
matches over the last two seasons, a conference record. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA100589-0033 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 116271 </DOCID>
