<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SCC TOPS CAL BAPTIST IN MEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
James Helmuth scored twice to lead the Southern California College men's soccer 
team to a 3-1 victory over visiting Cal Baptist Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Toby Ray scored three minutes into the game to give SCC a 1-0 lead, and Helmuth 
scored 32 minutes later to make it 2-0. Cal Baptist, which dropped to 4-7 
overall, 0-2 in the conference, cut the lead to 2-1 on Terry Cassidy's goal 10 
minutes into the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Helmuth scored at the 33:25 mark in the second half to seal the victory for SCC 
(3-9, 2-0). 
</P>
<P>
In California Collegiate Athletic Assn. men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
