<TEXT>
<P>
Miraleste's sophomore running backs Dan Sarner and Dan Crofton each rushed for 
more than 100 yards for the second consecutive week to lead the Marauders over 
Orange Lutheran, 18-14, in an Olympic League football opener. 
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Kristi White of the Cal State Dominguez Hills women's soccer team 
(11-0) scored her 11th goal of the season in a 2-1 win over Cal State Hayward 
to set a school record with 79 career points. 
</P>
<P>
Wilfred Rodriguez kicked a 46-yard field goal with no time remaining to lift 
Narbonne over L.A. Wilson, 23-20, and snap the Gauchos' 23-game losing streak, 
the longest skid in the state. 
</P>
<P>
Outside hitter Kerry House led the Loyola Marymount women's volleyball team to 
a three-match sweep to open West Coast Conference play, earning WCC Player of 
the Week honors. House had 41 kills and 80 digs. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Who's Not 
</P>
<P>
After three games, Inglewood's football team still has not scored a point. The 
Sentinels were hammered by Leuzinger, 40-0, last Thursday in a Bay League 
opener and have now been outscored, 96-0. 
</P>
<P>
Coast Christian, two-time defending CIF Eight-Man Small Division football 
champion, has fallen on hard times. The Saints fell to 0-3-1 following a 47-0 
loss to Chadwick last Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Palos Verdes failed to complete a pass in a 20-0 Bay League football loss to 
Hawthorne as quarterback Blake Anderson went 0 for 9 with one interception. The 
Sea Kings weren't much better on the ground, rushing for 127 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Not even the home-field advantage could help Harbor College's football team 
Saturday in a 56-0 loss to Bakersfield. The Seahawks (1-2) fell behind, 27-0, 
in the first half as Bakersfield piled up 273 total yards. 
</P>
