<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LAVERDE SCORES DECISIVE GOAL FOR CSUN, 2-1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Midfielder German Laverde scored an unassisted goal with two minutes remaining 
Wednesday to lift visiting Cal State Northridge to a 2-1 win over Cal Poly 
Pomona in a California Collegiate Athletic Assn. match. 
</P>
<P>
Laverde, a sophomore making his first start for the Matadors, stole the ball 
from a defender, dribbled to the left of the goal and fired a 23-yard shot with 
his left foot for his second goal of the season. 
</P>
<P>
"It was a rocket shot," Northridge Coach Marwan Ass'ad said. "German is known 
for having a very strong shot. He's really playing well." 
</P>
<P>
Northridge (5-2-2, 2-0 in conference play) took a 1-0 lead 30 minutes into the 
match when Jim Hofferber scored his team-high fifth goal on an assist from 
Scott Piri. 
</P>
<P>
Pomona (0-2 in conference play) evened the score with 20 minutes left in the 
match. 
</P>
<P>
