<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: 'BILL AND TED' SUCCESS IN VIDEO, TOO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Bill and Ted's Excellent Adventure," a sleeper box-office hit that grossed $39 
million, has duplicated this success on home video, inching up one notch into 
the coveted Top Five circle -- No. 5 on the Billboard rental chart. The Tom 
Selleck caper comedy, "Her Alibi," is doing better-than-expected rental 
business, jumping to No. 8 in its second chart week. "Skin Deep," the raunchy 
John Ritter comedy, cracked the Top 10, landing at No. 9. 
</P>
<P>
* The consensus was that "Fletch Lives," the further adventures of Chevy 
Chase's popular movie character, was just a mildly funny sequel. Still, it was 
a decent box-office draw ($32 million gross) and, at No. 13 in its second week 
on the rental chart, is certain to break into the Top 10. 
</P>
<P>
