<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: WEST HOLLYWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
SENIOR CENTER TO GET GUARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A full-time security guard will be on duty at the West Hollywood Senior Center 
in Plummer Park this month, in response to rising concern about the safety of 
staff and clients there. 
</P>
<P>
A letter to the Department of Human Services from Jewish Family Services, which 
operates the center, said the increasing number of transients, including the 
homeless, mentally ill and drug users, is causing volunteers, staff and clients 
to feel unsafe. The letter cited four incidents of violence that have occurred 
since June. 
</P>
<P>
The city council called for an evaluation by its staff of the security 
situation in early November. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
