<HEADLINE>
<P>
STORM DRAINS IN COMPTON, LONG BEACH TO BE CLEANED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Catch basins in Compton, Long Beach and portions of Los Angeles are to be 
cleaned under a $70,624 contract awarded by the county Board of Supervisors to 
Arsaka Research Co. of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Work is expected to begin this month and be completed in December. Storm drain 
catch basins in unincorporated areas surrounding the cities will be included in 
the clean-up project, Supervisor Deane Dana said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
