<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHO'S HOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rudy Ramirez of Bell Gardens rushed for 202 yards and scored four touchdowns in 
a 28-20 victory over Montebello. 
</P>
<P>
Ivan Wilson rushed for 165 yards and scored four touchdowns as South Gate High 
defeated L.A. Jordan, 34-0. 
</P>
<P>
Cerritos High won its first game, scoring two touchdowns in 28 seconds to come 
from behind and upset Lynwood, 21-19. 
</P>
<P>
John Glenn High junior fullback Paseka Teo rushed for 139 yards as the Eagles 
defeated Duarte, 27-12. 
</P>
<P>
Ron Papazian and Scott Jordan combined for 352 yards and six TDs as Whittier 
Christian beat Bell-Jeff, 42-0. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Who's Not 
</P>
<P>
Lakewood High has lost its last three games, including a 17-7 defeat last 
weekend to Marina, which snapped an 18-game losing streak. 
</P>
<P>
Brethren High has been outscored, 101-0, in its last two losses to Montclair 
Prep and Valley Christian. 
</P>
<P>
The La Serna Lancers are 0-4 and have been outscored, 124-29, under new coach 
Wayne Manzo. The team was 1-9 last year with Coach Ron Moncrief. 
</P>
<P>
Pioneer High has started the season 0-4 after going 1-9 last year. 
</P>
<P>
Millikan High of Long Beach had three first downs and 72 yards of total offense 
in a 10-6 loss to Schurr. 
</P>
