<P>
GUATEMALANS WILL SPEAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leaders of Guatemalan human rights groups Friday will discuss the wave of 
assassinations and bombings in their country during a panel discussion, 
"Guatemalan Repression on the Rise." 
</P>
<P>
Scheduled to speak are Margarita de Garcia, a representative of the Mutual 
Support Group; Mario Palma Acevedo, a member of the teachers union that 
recently carried out a two-month strike, and Acuaro Portillo, a member of the 
San Carlo University Students' Assn. 
</P>
<P>
The discussion will begin at 7 p.m. at the junior high classroom at Sequoyah 
School, 535 S. Pasadena Ave., Pasadena. There is no charge, and child care will 
be provided. For more information, call the Sequoyah Study Group at (818) 
795-4351. 
</P>
