<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: LA VERNE; 
</P>
<P>
E STREET PROJECT PROGRESSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bids for major construction on E Street will be opened by county supervisors 
Oct. 24. The construction will widen and improve E Street from Walnut Street in 
La Verne south past Brackett Field, along the Pomona-La Verne border to 
McKinley Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
The project will be jointly financed by Pomona, Laverne, the county, the state 
and the federal government. One lane will be added in each direction, and storm 
drains will be installed. The widening will require the removal of 52 trees, 
which will be replaced later under a separate contract. 
</P>
<P>
The work is scheduled to begin in January and to be completed in June. 
</P>
