<TEXT>
<P>
The final contingent of Cuban troops stationed in Ethiopia arrived in Havana 
aboard ship. The pullout of the 725 soldiers marked the end of the Cuban 
military presence in Ethiopia, which began in 1977 when the Marxist government 
was fighting a war with Somalia. Cuban troop strength in Ethiopia was at one 
time over 10,000. The returning soldiers were given special "internationalist" 
medals and promised preferential treatment in jobs. 
