<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some Lockheed Debt Ratings Reduced: The investment rating firm of Standard 
&amp; Poor's downgraded its rating of Lockheed's senior debt and preliminary 
shelf-registered debt to A from A plus. S&amp;P blamed the reductions on 
Lockheed's "weakened earnings prospects in a difficult defense procurement 
environment." It cited Lockheed's disclosure this week that it would report a 
$35-million third-quarter loss. S&amp;P asserted that the tight defense market 
would make it difficult for the company to compensate for the loss in earnings 
on the C-5B plane program. 
</P>
