<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUSTRALIAN PILOTS EASE WAGE DEMANDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SYDNEY, Australia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Australia's airline pilots said Wednesday that they were withdrawing the 30% 
pay increase demand at the heart of a dispute that has seriously disrupted the 
nation's domestic air services. 
</P>
<P>
John Raby, vice president of the Australian Federation of Air Pilots, told 
reporters that the pilots would instead seek an unspecified raise based on a 
25% increase in productivity. 
</P>
<P>
The federation submitted a new set of offers to the Industrial Relations 
Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
