<P>
PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The New York Mercantile Exchange named R. Patrick Thompson as its new 
president. He replaces Rosemary T. McFadden, who resigned in July. Thompson had 
been executive vice president of the exchange and its chief of staff since 
McFadden's departure. Before then, he was supervisory attorney for the New York 
regional office of the Commodity Futures Trading Commission division of 
enforcement. 
</P>
