<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
WOMAN DIES OF INJURIES FROM TRAFFIC COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Fountain Valley woman died Wednesday morning at UCI Medical Center in Orange 
after a traffic accident Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
Michelle Ann Camacho, 19, died at 3 a.m., the county coroner's office said. 
</P>
<P>
Police Sgt. Larry Griswold reported that a 16-year-old girl was making a left 
turn from Falcon Avenue onto Ward Street in Fountain Valley when her 1979 
Chrysler collided with Camacho's 1964 Volkswagen. 
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old and her 15-year-old sister, who was riding with her, were 
treated for minor injuries at the scene and released. 
</P>
<P>
Police are investigating the accident to determine responsibility. 
</P>
</TEXT>
