<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FULLERTON; 
</P>
<P>
EXPLOSIONS NEAR CSUF THOUGHT TO BE A PRANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In what police are calling a prank, residents of the University Village 
apartment complex near Cal State Fullerton were awakened at 4 a.m. Wednesday by 
seven loud explosions. 
</P>
<P>
A Fullerton police spokesman said no injuries were reported. Residents, 
primarily students, called the police to the Oxford Avenue complex. When 
officers arrived, they also heard explosions. They found nine plastic beverage 
bottles -- seven of which had already exploded -- containing an unidentified 
gas. 
</P>
<P>
The Orange County Sheriff Department bomb squad defused two of the containers 
holding the mysterious mixture. The gas had not been identified as of Wednesday 
night. Police are looking for suspects. 
</P>
<P>
The culprit did not apparently want anyone or anything to be hurt by the 
blasts, officers said, because the bombs were placed far enough away from the 
apartments to avoid injury or property damage. 
</P>
<P>
Police officials speculated Wednesday that whoever mixed the chemicals must 
have known that they would blow up after sitting for a while and probably did 
it as a prank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
