<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISNEY CHARACTERS BOMBARDED AS COMPANY OFFERS PARIS SHARES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mickey Mouse, Donald Duck and Pluto met a shower of ketchup and eggs on the 
steps of the Bourse, the Paris stock exchange, today. 
</P>
<P>
The sticky barrage was hurled by about 100 French communist demonstrators 
seeking to spoil a party organized to announce the offer price of shares in 
Europe's Disneyland. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Eisner, chairman of Walt Disney Co., who was in Paris to announce the 
offer price of $11.20 a share, was also a target for the missiles, along with 
people dressed up in suits depicting other Disney characters. 
</P>
<P>
The shares are being floated to help finance construction of a new Disney theme 
park on the outskirts of Paris. 
</P>
<P>
Demonstrators yelling "Mickey go home!" and "EuroDisneyland: dirty deal of the 
century!" also showered onlookers with fake $500 bills as Disney executives 
looked on. No police were present. 
</P>
<P>
Eisner said the demonstration had nothing to do with Disney. "Those people were 
asking for more money from the government. These local issues are not related 
to the Disney company." 
</P>
<P>
"Who could possibly be against Cinderella and Snow White? EuroDisneyland is 
going to create 12,000 jobs in France," said Disney's European chief, Frank 
Fitzpatrick. 
</P>
<P>
Plans to celebrate the share launch with dancing in front of the Bourse were 
called off after the demonstration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
