<P>
EASY GOER FACES TOUGH COMPETITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Easy Goer takes a four-race winning streak into the $1,099,000 Jockey Club Gold 
Cup on Saturday against a seven-horse field that includes the only other horse 
to beat archrival Sunday Silence this year. 
</P>
<P>
The 1 1/2-mile Gold Cup will be Easy Goer's last race before once again 
confronting Sunday Silence in the Breeders' Cup Classic on Nov. 4 at Gulfstream 
Park. In all likelihood, Horse of the Year will be at stake. 
</P>
<P>
First, however, Easy Goer must contend with a field, entered today, which 
includes the 3-year-old colt Prized, who beat Sunday Silence in the Swaps 
Stakes one start after Easy Goer beat him at the Belmont. 
</P>
<P>
Easy Goer will be ridden by Pat Day. Eddie Delahoussaye gets the ride aboard 
Prized. Also in the field will be three horses Easy Goer already has beaten -- 
Forever Silver, Cryptoclearance and Its Acedemic -- along with Jack of Clubs 
and Impersonator. 
</P>
